what is the ratio of people in uber/raiding guilds vs people in smaller casual guilds.  <br>
- I think the playerbase for this game is a LOT older than most people think.  They have real world things, like families and jobs to consider first.<br>
- I myself think their are more casual players.<br>
Why aren't we getting some consideration?  (and no I'm sorry the promise of EQ2 does not cut it.  I bought THIS game, not vaporware for some future time).<br>
<br>
My guild has about 24 people it can muster for a raid and if we are lucky we might get some uber guild's hand me down mob (&quot;it doesn't drop anything we want anymore, you can have it&quot;).  The content that would actually be fun for us has either been farmed by a single group of EP/Time equiped people or its not up for another 2.5 days.  <br>
<br>
LDoN raids were supposed to be for smaller groups (like 36 people) but hey you have to be time equiped to do one and at that point you don't need the gear from it.  I've heard no mention of the dificulty being scalable so if you can only muster up 24 people you are SoL.<br>
<br>
We as a guild can not get flagged for the elemental planes - we don't have enough bodies.  That means we either have to tag along with another guild or we have to form an alliance.<br>
<br>
Being a guest on another guild's raid you are tolerated at best.  No guild wants to run the risk of wasting hours of time only to have some jerk mess it up, so they are hesitant to have guest on the more important raids (or there is no room).  The loot will be retained in the guild for DKP bidding so the &quot;guest&quot; will have no chance at loot.  If they are lucky they might be thrown some scraps (like parchments).  I've been a visitor on many raids - oh boy what fun, I feel like a red-headed step child on the raid and I feel like I'm betraying my guild for trying to do stuff without them, that they can't do.<br>
<br>
Forming an alliance involves so much effort and politics that most guild leaders don't want to do it.  This is supposed to be a game remember - not another job.  And if you do get an alliance formed you still have issues with target selection, co-ordination and if just a few people think they have been slighted or their feelings get hurt, the whole thing can unravel.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>It would be nice</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> if Sony took a sample cross section of their player base for this kiss-up session and not just the raiding guilds.<br>
<br>
For anyone who is going,  here's what I'd like to see.<br>
- Faster respawns on boss/quest/flag mobs to prevent guilds from cock blocking others. <br>
- If you can't do that then create an instanced/retry system.  Where a group of people can instance an event at their convenience.  This would allow smaller guilds to schedule events verses real life more easily.  Then regardless of the outcome each participant is tagged for that event and can't do it for a preset amount of time (maybe a day or two).<br>
- retune the LDoN raids so people migh actually do them.<br>
<br>
This game has too many time sinks, get rid of them. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><br>
